4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, certain utilities, including
6 those with a gross annual income of two hundred fifty
7 million dollars or less, may be reimbursed for costs
8 incurred to relocate utility facilities required for
9 road construction pursuant to an order of the Director
10 of Transportation, subject to certain conditions.
11 This bill would add conditions to the payment of
12 costs by the state for utility facility relocations by
13 these certain utilities.
14 This bill would require the director to
15 reimburse utilities with a gross annual income over two
16 hundred fifty million dollars for costs incurred in
17 relocating utility facilities pursuant to an order of
18 the director, subject to certain conditions.
19 This bill would also require the director to
20 submit an annual report to the Legislature that
21 provides information related to such payments.
22
23
24 A BILL
25 TO BE ENTITLED
26 AN ACT
27
28 Relating to public highways; to amend Section 23-1-5,
