152 (h) For purposes of this section, when a utility
153 facility relocation requires the relocation of transmission
154 lines and distribution lines, the relocation of transmission
155 lines and distribution lines shall be considered separate and
156 distinct utility facility relocations.
157 (i) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, if a
158 utility begins a utility facility relocation pursuant to this
159 section and the Director of Transportation determines and
160 orders a revision to the utility facility relocation for the
161 same project before completion of the project, the state shall
162 pay all further costs of relocating the utility facility after
